# shadcn/ui Components

Use **shadcn/ui** as the primary component library. Components are copied into the repo (not imported from a package) and live in `packages/ui/src/components/ui/`.

## Adding Components

Always use the CLI — never copy-paste manually:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component> --cwd apps/web
```

Components are added to `apps/web/components/ui/` and should then be moved/re-exported from `packages/ui` if shared across apps.

## Usage Rules

- **Prefer shadcn components** over custom HTML elements for all standard UI patterns (buttons, inputs, dialogs, badges, tables, etc.).
- **Do not modify** files inside `components/ui/` directly — extend behaviour by wrapping, not editing generated code.
- Wrap shadcn primitives in a named component when you need to add project-specific props or defaults:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — using raw shadcn Button with repeated variants everywhere
<Button variant="destructive" size="sm">Delete</Button>

// ✅ GOOD — wrap with project-specific defaults
export function DeleteButton({ children, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return <Button variant="destructive" size="sm" {...props}>{children}</Button>;
}
```

## Theming

- Configure design tokens in `apps/web/app/globals.css` using CSS variables (the shadcn default approach).
- Do not hard-code colours — always use the CSS variable tokens (e.g. `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`).

## Components to Use per Feature

| UI Need | shadcn Component |
|---|---|
| Dashboard / widget list | `Table`, `Badge` |
| Dashboard selector dropdown | `Select` or `Combobox` |
| Connection config form | `Input`, `Label`, `Button` |
| Wellcheck results | `Card`, `Badge`, `ScrollArea` |
| Error / warning indicators | `Alert`, `Badge` (variant) |
| Loading state | `Skeleton` |
| Code snippet display | wrap `pre` inside a `Card` |
